metadata.name: The Firewalker
metadata.description:
Firewalking is a symbolic act that has been used in many cultures and traditions throughout history to represent a variety of concepts, including purification, transcendence, and transformation. Similarly, the deconstruction and reconstruction of one's identity is a process of personal transformation that can involve letting go of old ways of thinking and being, and embracing new and different aspects of oneself.  
Furthermore, beauty is not just about physical appearance, but also about inner qualities such as resilience, strength, and determination. A Firewalker, who must overcome their fear and discomfort in order to walk across burning coals, embodies these qualities and can serve as a powerful symbol of inner beauty and strength.
